   <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
      <p class="- topic/p ">This procedure, based on Policy EHS-01-103 Life Saving Protocol- Working at Heights establishes requirements for performing work on potentially unstable surface, using equipment to work at the elevated level (elevating work platforms) on a sloping or slippery surface where it is difficult for people to maintain their balance, near an unprotected open edge (near incomplete stairwells), near a hole or shaft (trenches, service pits) or on a fragile surface(roofs).Working at heights can include tasks where activity is carried out on any structure or plant being constructed or installed, demolished or dismantled, inspected, tested, repaired, or cleaned.</p>
